Smart Bookmark App
Built by Vinesh Gottipati
Live Demo
Production URL:
https://smart-bookmark-app-gq1y.vercel.app
GitHub Repository:
https://github.com/vineshgottipati/smart-bookmark-app
Project Overview
This is a full-stack Smart Bookmark Manager built using Next.js (App Router) and Supabase.
•	Sign in using Google OAuth only
•	Add bookmarks (Title + URL)
•	View only their own bookmarks (Private access)
•	See real-time updates across tabs
•	Delete their bookmarks
•	Open bookmarks in a new tab
•	Log out securely
Tech Stack
•	Next.js 16 (App Router)
•	Supabase
•	Authentication (Google OAuth)
•	PostgreSQL Database
•	Row Level Security (RLS)
•	Realtime subscriptions
•	Tailwind CSS
•	Vercel (Deployment)
Authentication
•	Google OAuth only (No email/password login)
•	Supabase Auth used for session management
•	Production redirect URLs configured
•	Environment variables handled securely
Database Design
Table: bookmarks
•	id - uuid
•	title - text
•	url - text
•	user_id - uuid
•	created_at - timestamp
Row Level Security (RLS)
•	Users can SELECT their own bookmarks
•	Users can INSERT bookmarks where user_id = auth.uid()
•	Users can DELETE their own bookmarks
Realtime Feature
Supabase Realtime is enabled on the bookmarks table. If a user opens two tabs and adds or deletes a bookmark in one tab, the other tab updates automatically without refresh.
Deployment
The application is deployed using Vercel.
Environment Variables used in production:
•	NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
•	NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
Problems Faced & Solutions
•	Google OAuth Redirect Error (redirect_uri_mismatch) - Configured correct redirect URLs in Google Cloud Console and Supabase Auth.
•	Supabase Environment Variables Build Error - Added environment variables in Vercel project settings.
•	Next.js 'use client' Order Error - Ensured 'use client' is the first line in client components.
•	Logout / Session Refresh Issues - Used supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange listener properly.
Architecture Notes
•	Client-side Supabase initialization
•	Dynamic rendering to prevent prerender crashes
•	Strict RLS enforcement
•	Real-time subscription channel per table
•	Clean separation of logic and UI
How To Run Locally
git clone https://github.com/vineshgottipati/smart-bookmark-app.git
cd smart-bookmark-app
npm install
npm run dev
Add .env.local with:
•	NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_url
•	NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_key
